---

<Layout 
  title="Enterprise Software - Cloud Intelligence"
  description="When prototype solutions fail and you need enterprise-grade software that scales, performs, and complies with regulations."
  keywords="enterprise software, legacy modernization, performance engineering, compliance, scalability, technical rescue"
>
  <PageHero 
    title="Enterprise Software"
    subtitle="When Prototypes Break, Call the Pros"
    description="Transform failing projects into enterprise-grade solutions that scale, perform, and meet the highest standards of reliability and security."
  />
  
  <section class="intro-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="intro-content">
        <h2>From Prototype Panic to Production Ready</h2>
        <p class="large-text">
          We've all been there. The quick prototype worked beautifully in the demo. 
          But now it's crashing under real load, security is a nightmare, and compliance auditors are asking uncomfortable questions.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>That's where we come in.</strong> We're the team enterprises call when their "move fast and break things" 
          approach has broken everything, and they need professionals to build something that actually works at scale.
        </p>
        
        <div class="warning-box">
          <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è Warning Signs You Need Enterprise Software</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Your app crashes when more than 50 people use it</li>
            <li>You're storing passwords in plain text (yes, really)</li>
            <li>Your database queries take 30+ seconds</li>
            <li>You have no idea where your data is or who can access it</li>
            <li>Compliance auditors are having nightmares about your system</li>
            <li>Your "temporary" prototype is now mission-critical</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="rescue-scenarios">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Common Rescue Scenarios</h2>
      <div class="scenarios-grid">
        {rescueScenarios.map((scenario) => (
          <div class="scenario-card">
            <h3>{scenario.title}</h3>
            <p class="scenario-description">{scenario.description}</p>
            <div class="problem-solution">
              <div class="problem">
                <strong>The Problem:</strong> {scenario.problem}
              </div>
              <div class="arrow">‚Üí</div>
              <div class="solution">
                <strong>Our Solution:</strong> {scenario.solution}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="intro-content">
        <h2>Enterprise-Grade Solutions</h2>
        <p>
          We don't just fix broken prototypes‚Äîwe architect solutions that handle the demands of real enterprise environments. 
          From day one, we build for scale, security, and compliance.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="features-grid">
        {features.map((feature) => (
          <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">{feature.icon}</div>
            <h3>{feature.title}</h3>
            <p>{feature.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="stats-section">
        <h2>Why Enterprises Trust Us</h2>
        <div class="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat-item">
            <div class="stat-number">99.99%</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Uptime Guarantee</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-item">
            <div class="stat-number">$400M+</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Transactions Processed</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-item">
            <div class="stat-number">1M+</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Concurrent Users Supported</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-item">
            <div class="stat-number">100%</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Security Audits Passed</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="cta-section">
        <h2>Ready to Go from Prototype to Production?</h2>
        <p>Stop patching problems. Start building solutions that scale.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="cta-button">Get Emergency Help</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-grid">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What makes enterprise software different from regular applications?</h3>
          <p>Enterprise software is built for scale, security, and compliance from day one. It handles thousands of concurrent users, implements enterprise-grade security, meets regulatory requirements, and includes comprehensive monitoring, disaster recovery, and audit trails that prototype solutions typically lack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can you rescue a failing project that's already in production?</h3>
          <p>Yes, we specialize in technical rescue missions. We conduct thorough assessments, identify critical issues, implement immediate fixes to stabilize the system, then systematically rebuild components to meet enterprise standards while maintaining business continuity.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How do you handle legacy system modernization?</h3>
          <p>We use a phased approach: analyze existing systems, design modern architecture, create integration bridges, migrate data safely, train teams, and gradually replace legacy components. This ensures minimal disruption while modernizing your technology stack.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What security and compliance standards do you support?</h3>
          <p>We implement comprehensive security frameworks including SOC 2, HIPAA, PCI DSS, GDPR, ISO 27001, and industry-specific regulations. Our solutions include encryption, access controls, audit logging, vulnerability management, and automated compliance reporting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How do you ensure system performance at enterprise scale?</h3>
          <p>We use performance engineering principles including load testing, database optimization, caching strategies, CDN implementation, auto-scaling, and monitoring. Our systems are designed to handle millions of users with sub-second response times and 99.99% uptime.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What's your approach to mission-critical system development?</h3>
          <p>Mission-critical systems require redundancy, monitoring, disaster recovery, and zero-downtime deployments. We implement high-availability architectures, comprehensive testing, gradual rollouts, and 24/7 monitoring to ensure systems never fail when they matter most.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

